Secure Multi-User Linux Server

## Objective
To create a secure multi-user Linux environment with proper user management,
SSH hardening, and firewall configuration.

## Step 1: User and Group Management
- Created a group named devops
- Added users ishant_dev and test_user
- Assigned users to the devops group
- Verified users using /etc/passwd

## Step 2: SSH Hardening
- Disabled root login
- Changed default SSH settings
- Restarted SSH service and verified access

## Step 3: Firewall Configuration
- Enabled UFW
- Allowed SSH traffic
- Blocked unnecessary ports
- Verified firewall status

## Outcome
- Secure multi-user system created
- Only authorized users can access via SSH
- Server is protected using firewall rules

## Tools Used
- Linux (Ubuntu)
- SSH
- UFW
- systemctl
